Citation.sTitle: Density and Viscosity of Several Aldehydes Fragrance Compounds in Their Binary Mixtures with Ethanol at (298.15 K, 308.15 K, and 318.15 K)
Citation.sAbstract: Density and viscosity for binary mixtures of hexanal, octanal, nonanal, and decanal with ethanol over the whole composition range have been measured at three different temperatures (298.15, 308.15, and 318.15) K and atmospheric pressure. Redlich-Kister-type polynomial equations were fitted to the calculated excess molar volumes and viscosity deviations.
